In this op-ed, President Obama discusses the partnership between Turkey and the United States. He emphasizes the long-standing alliance between the two countries and the shared commitment to security. The President also mentions the importance of increasing trade and creating more jobs, as well as addressing regional challenges such as the Israeli-Palestinian conflict and supporting democratic transitions in Egypt and Libya. Additionally, President Obama highlights the need to work together to end the Syrian civil war and provide humanitarian relief to Syrian refugees. He concludes by expressing his eagerness to consult with Prime Minister Erdogan on global challenges and his belief that the alliance between Turkey and the United States will continue to deliver security, prosperity, and progress for both nations.